\{bmc IDF20890.bmp\}\tab \b \i logical value \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20474.bmp\}\tab \b \i text terminated by binar null (ASCIIZ) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20475.bmp\}\tab \b \i text terminated by end of line (CR and LF) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20476.bmp\}\tab \b \i text with fixed length \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20510.bmp\}\tab \b \i length of text with fixed length \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20729.bmp\}\tab \b \i text is in UNICODE format \i0 \b0 (2 bytes) \par
\{bmc IDF20477.bmp\}\tab \b \i item (ICO) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20478.bmp\}\tab \b \i picture (BMP, JPG and some AVI) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20479.bmp\}\tab \b \i sound (WAV, MP3) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20480.bmp\}\tab \b \i music (MID, RMI) \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20632.bmp\}\tab \b \i sprite (SPR) \i0 \b0 \par
\par
The data elements can be used in a similar manner like the variables. By writing into an element a write is performed to the output file, by reading an element's value this value is readed from the input file. If an operation error occurs, the {\uldb operation error flag}{\v 20509} is set. A format error during reading item, picture, sound, music or sprite elements will not cause a change in the state of the read operation pointer.\par
\par
The \b \i logical value \i0 \b0 element uses 1 byte to store a value. The logical value "Yes" is written as number 1, the logical value "No" is written as number 0. During the reading any number that is not equal 0 is considered to be the logical value "Yes".\par
\par
When reading a picture, the reading of some AVI files using non-compressed 16 bit data (format of the video sequence saved by some TV cards) is supported in addition to the reading of the BMP and JPEG formats. By reading the first picture from the beginning of the AVI file information about the file format is determined, which is used also on reading the subsequent pictures from the AVI file. The picture writing always takes place in the BMP format.\par
\par
When reading a sound, the MPEG Layer-3 (MP3) format is supported. To {\uldb play it back}{\v 20299}, an installation of a driver may be necessary. The sound writing always takes place in the WAW format.\par
\par
The \b \i length of text with fixed length \i0 \b0 element defines the length of a fixed length text (not the file data, but an auxiliary internal variable being concerned).\par
\par
The \b \i text is in UNICODE format \i0 \b0 element is a switch indicating that the texts are loaded and stored in the UNICODE format. Normally, the texts are loaded and stored in the Windows default format, one character corresponding to one file byte. In the UNICODE code characters are stored into 2 bytes. The text is not dependent on the national code system; its disadvantage are higher demands on the file size.\par
